  "text": "By strict definition BLPACR strains are amoxicillin/clavulanate resistant (CLSI breakpoint ≥8 mg/L), although when genetic criteria are used gBLPACR isolates are often amoxicillin/clavulanate susceptible (MIC range 0.25-2 mg/L). [CITATION_1] All gBLPACR isolates of this study (n¼ 7) were amoxicillin/clavulanate susceptible (MIC range 2 -4 mg/L), although we were unable to demonstrate a decrease in susceptibility attributed to the PBP3 substitutions in these isolates in comparison with the gBLPAR isolates (MIC range 1 -4 mg/L).",
